const title = "Wyoming Mineral Rights | MineralWise";
const description = "Wyoming mineral rights contribute more than $2.2 billion dollars in the form of taxes to the state and local economies of Wyoming. Wyoming is seventh in oil production, second in gas production, and first in helium production in the United States.Major Oil and Gas Fields in WyomingBruff FieldElk BasinFogary Creek FieldGarland FieldHamilton DomeHouse Creek FieldJonah FieldLake Ridge FieldLost Soldier FieldMadden FieldOregon BasinPainter Reservoir EastPinedale FieldPRB Coal BedSalt Creek FieldSandard Draw FieldSpring Creek South FieldWamsutter FieldOil and Gas Companies Active in WyomingDevon Energy ProductionEncana Oil and GasLance Oil &amp;amp; Gas CompanyMerit Energy CompanyQuestar Exploration and ProductionShell Rocky Mountain ProductionUltra ResourcesWexpro CompanyWilliams Production RMTYates Petroleum CorporationWyoming Mineral Rights LinksWyoming Oil and Gas Conservation Commission: http://wogcc.state.wy.us/Additional ReadingOil &amp;amp; Gas 101 – General information for mineral rights owners. Start here if you’re a newbie.";

